metadata.name: Universal Rayhatcher #418
metadata.description:
# What is this?

This is 6942 characters of highly experimental code.

This is a version of my rayhatcher framework (see https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/rayhatching-evolution) that can do literally everything. Or, at least anything you can do within 512 characters of Javascript code. Which is slightly more than a mortal brain can comprehend.

This is my answer to the question: What is the least restrictive set of parameters for fx(params)?

# Should I be minting this?

Depends if you know and like building SDF formulas. Otherwise probably not. Like I said, this is highly experimental code. But it's definitely worth checking the collection and/or secondary for cool stuff that is already minted.

# How does it work?

The minter designs an SDF (Signed Distance Function) which is rendered using my rayhatcher algorithm. They then use the SDF formula in the SDF Code parameter. It's not very complicated, just efficient.

You can press "h" to load the documentation and read about how everything works. Or you can press "d" to read the dev docs. 

# Anything else?

Don't forget that the "Title Seed" param also becomes the "Title" feature of the mint, so make it count.

The params, including the SDF code actually get saved on-chain. Even better, all params and the entire code required to reproduce the image are included in the SVG when saved. See https://twitter.com/piterpasma/status/1649071912742420482 .

metadata.name: Ornamental Tree #107
metadata.description:
A simple tree in a grassy field. Released as a thank you gift to holders of Orchard, Grove, and Deep Forest.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px

Common Features:
- One of three seasons: spring, summer, or fall
- 50/50 square or circle shaped trees
- Percent distance haze
- Neutral or blue sky color
- 50/50 color or background tinted clouds
- Color tints for highlights and shadows
- If spring or summer, 50/50 chance of flowers
- Smooth rolling hills or not

metadata.name: Original Threads  #66
metadata.description:
Original Threads is an exploration of the winding of digital thread. Originally developed as an experiment of recreating rolls of thread in p5js, this collaboration of efforts combines se.nao.neste's core algorithmic work with Liam's drive to push as much coherent variety into a generator as possible.

At its core, this work wraps threads around a central point, subscribing to various rules as it does so. The movement of the thread is determined by the angular momentum combined with a "wander" factor.

One of the most exciting parts of the development of this algorithm was discovering and exploiting the various idiosyncracies (the peculiarities) of the drawing algorithm - the broken lines when the stroke is above a certain weight, the "burning" of the heavily layered shadows etc. - these "mistakes" we've loved and cherished and became an intrinsic part of the artistic expression of the piece.

Double-tap / hit "s" to download an image.
Add a URL parameter of "dpr" (for example ?dpr=4) to increse the resolution.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details

metadata.name: Deep Forest #283
metadata.description:
I love being in nature and impressionistic paintings. Deep Forest is my latest attempt to combine them with JavaScript. The editions will range from open, sparse forests to lush, dense, leafy wonderlands. Fall editions may render as Klimpt-style birch forests - my original inspiration for this work.

Best viewed on a computer. It may take a few seconds to start drawing and, depending on complexity, several minutes to finish rendering. In live view, press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px.

Features:
- One of the four seasons
- Rare 10% night version with 50/50 for normal fireflies or "fire" fireflies. Night will only be spring or summer.
- Amount of atmosphere/haze
- Horizon line near the middle or 30% "high horizon" near the top
- Tint from one of 8 light and 7 shadow colors
- Strength of the light and shadow color tint
- Mixed tree trunks or 30% all birch
- 50/50 moss on tree trunks
- One of 8 flower colors in spring or summer
- One of 4 perspective transforms
- Straight, curved out, or 30% curved inward trunks
- 50/50 grass in fall or winter
- 85% will have flowers in spring and summer
- 95% will have underbrush
- 50/50 clouds or solid background
- 50/50 solid background will be vertical or swirls
- Ground hill height

metadata.name: BWEEPS  #180
metadata.description:
A minimalist, black-and-white generative profile picture (PFP) created to commemorate one-year anniversary of Bwople project by Gengoya. The artwork is derived from an initial sketch of Bwople which, despite being not the one that was chosen, still managed to captivate interests. The project provides a unique glimpse into an alternate universe in which Bwople could have been represented.

All images are hand-drawn work by Gengoya and composed by Vector Recite using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

To download the full size image on fx(hash):
- Click "open" below the image
- Left click on the image, a "Download image" button will appear on the bottom right.
- Click the "Download image" button.

metadata.name: SoulSea #237
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu
